{
  "texts": [
    "If ■ i ↓y is nonempty but does not contain a maximum element, then i y is undefined.",
    "◁The following fact is a straightforward consequence of the definitions just given.Fact 4.38 (Principal Partial-State Frames).",
    "Let F = ⟨S, ⊑, {R i } i∈I, P ⟩ be such that ⟨S, ⊑⟩ is a poset, R i is a binary relation on S, and P is the set of all principal downsets in ⟨S, ⊑⟩ plus ∅.Then the following are equivalent:1.",
    "F is a partial-state frame;2.",
    "P is closed under the operations ∩, ⊃, and ■ i from Definition 2.1;3. the extension ⟨S ⊥, ⊑ ⊥ ⟩ of ⟨S, ⊑⟩ (Definition 4.23) is a bounded implicative semilattice on which the operation i defined from R i ⊥ (Definition 4.23) is a total operation.In addition to the closure requirements on P in partial-state frames, there is the requirement in possibility frames that P ⊆ RO(S, ⊑) (Definition 2.21)."
  ]
}